Microsoft and Inflection AI

From Bloomberg
<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-03-19/microsoft-hires-deepmin=
d-co-founder-suleyman-to-run-consumer-ai>
:

Microsoft Corp. has named Mustafa Suleyman head of its consumer artificial
intelligence business, hiring most of the staff from his Inflection AI
startup as the software giant seeks to fend off Alphabet Inc.=E2=80=99s Goo=
gle in
the fiercely contested market for AI products. Suleyman, who co-founded
Google=E2=80=99s DeepMind, will report to Chief Executive Officer Satya Nad=
ella and
oversee a range of projects, such as integrating an AI Copilot into Windows
and adding conversational elements to the Bing search engine. His hiring
will put Microsoft=E2=80=99s consumer AI work under one leader for the firs=
t time.

Inflection, a rival of Microsoft=E2=80=99s key AI partner OpenAI, is shifti=
ng to
selling AI software to businesses but will continue operating its Pi
consumer chatbot business for now. Kar=C3=A9n Simonyan, Inflection=E2=80=99=
s co-founder,
will join Microsoft as chief scientist for the new consumer AI group.

This is a bizarre move that only makes sense once you collect a number of
different details in one place.

First, from Inflection=E2=80=99s website <https://inflection.ai/the-new-inf=
lection>:

Our plan going forward is to lean into our AI studio business, where custom
generative AI models are crafted, tested and fine tuned for commercial
customers. Our success at training, tailoring and improving the performance
of large AI models makes us uniquely well placed to be the AI platform for
businesses around the world.

As part of this, we=E2=80=99re thrilled to announce that we will now host
Inflection-2.5 on Microsoft Azure helping us get it into the hands of
creators everywhere. We=E2=80=99ll also be ensuring it comes to other cloud=
 hosting
platforms in the near future. The API itself isn=E2=80=99t available today,=
 but
will be up and running very soon. To sign up for early access and help us
test it, please register your interest here. Between API access and select
high-level partnerships with great customers, our AIs can now spread to
even larger new user bases while helping put cutting-edge AI capabilities
in the hands of thousands of developers.

Second, from Forbes
<https://www.forbes.com/sites/alexkonrad/2024/03/19/inflection-abandons-cha=
tgpt-challenger-ceo-suleyman-joins-microsoft/>
:

Microsoft is not taking any equity position in Inflection AI as part of the
shift, a second source added, nor will it be acquiring any of Inflection=E2=
=80=99s
intellectual property. Inflection, Microsoft and Suleyman declined to
comment beyond their respective posts. In a statement posted to LinkedIn,
that professional network=E2=80=99s cofounder Reid Hoffman =E2=80=94 also I=
nflection=E2=80=99s
third cofounder and a board director =E2=80=94 wrote
<https://www.linkedin.com/posts/reidhoffman_the-new-inflection-an-important=
-change-to-activity-7175943405720539136-icUr>:
=E2=80=9CThis agreement with Microsoft means that all of Inflection=E2=80=
=99s investors
will have a good outcome today, and I anticipate good future upside.=E2=80=
=9D

Of note: Microsoft was already an investor in Inflection AI before Tuesday.
But that =E2=80=9Cgood outcome=E2=80=9D didn=E2=80=99t include investors re=
ceiving any cash from
the company in the form of a partial exit, a source with knowledge said.
Hoffman may have been instead alluding to a financial arrangement,
previously undisclosed by Microsoft and Inflection and first reported by
Forbes, as part of its license of Inflection=E2=80=99s API, multiple source=
s said.
By that arrangement, Inflection investors could be made whole on their
committed capital, though not immediately, they added.

Inflection will focus now on providing an application programming
interface, or API, to other businesses =E2=80=94 a major shift for a compan=
y that
had focused until recently on Pi, its chatbot alternative to OpenAI=E2=80=
=99s
ChatGPT and Anthropic=E2=80=99s Claude. It will host that API on Microsoft=
=E2=80=99s cloud
service as well as others, the source added. In its own post, Inflection
claimed that PI had =E2=80=9Cmillions=E2=80=9D of weekly users. Those peopl=
e would continue
to have access, at least for now, as the company claimed =E2=80=9Cthere wil=
l be no
immediate changes to the service.=E2=80=9D

Finally, from The Information
<https://www.theinformation.com/articles/microsoft-backed-inflection-arrang=
es-unusual-payout-for-startups-investors>
:

Microsoft=E2=80=99s decision to hire most of the staff of Inflection AI, in=
cluding
co-founders Mustafa Suleyman and Kar=C3=A9n Simonyan, leaves the would-be O=
penAI
rival a shell of its former self. But Inflection has arranged an unusual
deal for investors that should take the sting out of that blow.

At the same time it revealed the staff departures, Inflection disclosed a
