kOnJlYWQgYXJ0aWNsZTpyZWFkIGFzc2V0OnJlYWQgY2F0ZWdvcnk6cmVhZCBlbnRpdGxlbWVudH=
MiLCJzdWIiOiJSc2V1WUU4amdIZVBwV0pmMWZBYjRDIiwidXNlIjoiYWNjZXNzIn0.l4kfDDmKS=
JwydHCTTril-ekjOBI2D4Ch01LfsIKPzPA-XJELyI1SNtH2myQnwJeblb5EqbGq2oafg0pP_6nX=
-jGHKy9V29i2GlaXaVcU3bwmDAtApd6p3bBQ8gvCszs3binYIpBnstXFdEuTYo-rWDvDAdg9N7k=
al_N_oG2Wz3B_UF1LP9nilS4iz3yslXATTqtxKIsW8xKDZyYLr6yLUP9V1Goyg5pWAc3eEJadgR=
E2RIgRBlMXYG-KwWGfJpkVs-1paBXccSU1K_PxagAyac6wU0wsdDgBpl3YNUm0jAv1dCGih_0Dl=
53W6KTEYVu-L7P9Rtpp1rSyUEa2uIbmGA>
why Big Tech looks poised to dominate AI, including the importance of cloud
infrastructure, data, and existing distribution channels. It=E2=80=99s nota=
ble,
though, that a huge amount of the investment into AI startups, particularly
the ambitious ones actually building models, is also coming from Big Tech:
they can de-risk those investments by providing credits instead of dollars
as Microsoft has, or by double-dipping on GPU sales like Nvidia is.
Traditional investors, meanwhile, don=E2=80=99t have a clear exit if acquis=
itions
are off the table.

Big Tech, though, is making it work anyways: Microsoft is definitely
getting the Inflection team and model, and maybe also the GPUs. Meanwhile,
the one traditional venture firm on Inflection=E2=80=99s cap table was Grey=
lock,
where Reid Hoffman, the only Inflection co-founder not going to work at
Microsoft, is partner. Hoffman, of course, doesn=E2=80=99t need to go to Mi=
crosoft
because he, conveniently enough, is already on the behemoth=E2=80=99s board=
, which
means he was perfectly placed to engineer a scenario where Greylock and the
other investors are poised to get their money back for a failed startup.

In other words, this is an acquisition in everything but name, just in the
most convoluted way possible; the FTC can pat itself on the back, I guess,
while Microsoft probably pays less than they might have otherwise, and
every other would-be entrepreneur checks if their investors are sitting on
any big company boards, and if they can make any irrational GPU purchases
to make the relationship worth the trouble.
